es is prefigured. The second two register certain effects of Wagnerism that are not just ideological but make themselves felt in a new political configuration of the "national" and the "social."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 4aLiterary Studies -- General Criticism and Theory. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Composers & Musicians.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150362241840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503622418423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503622418/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles